    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/102.html" title="RTA 102 - Creative Processes" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 102</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Creative Processes</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This introductory course focuses on principles, theories and practices of content development for a variety of media genres, formats and distribution platforms. Students explore the development of creative and fact-based content by using processes such as rapid prototyping, iterative design, story-chasing and script writing. Students emerge from the course with an understanding of how to take their creative ideas from inception to the creation of compelling content.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lab: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
