           <li class="courseListItem" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0 0 10px;list-style-image:none;list-style-type:none;">
           









  
    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/103.html" title="RTA 103 - Digital Media Production I" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 103</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Digital Media Production I</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Through a combination of lecture and hands-on workshops, students will broaden their understanding of digital media, develop a critical understanding of the role of digital media in contemporary life, and become conscious consumers and creators of technology and digital media content. Students will be introduced to principles of visual design and communication, and will learn how to use digital media production software for graphic design, web-native production and time-based media.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 1 hr. Lab: 2 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
