    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/180.html" title="RTA 180 - Music and Film" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 180</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Music and Film</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">The use of music with film has evolved from early stereotyped borrowing of nineteenth century classical European repertoire to newly created scores that enhance and support the dramatic themes of the film.  This course explores the relationship between music and film, the functions and effects of music and how the music supports or plays against the visual images.  Analysis of selected film genres will demonstrate how music can strengthen the film's dramatic themes. (Formerly MUS 110)</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
