    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/210.html" title="RTA 210 - Media History" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 210</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Media History</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course traces the history of media from the first radio broadcast to today's transmedia storyworlds. Students consider the main forces which shaped our media industry: technological change, commercial imperatives, creative aspirations, demographic trends and government policy and regulation. By looking at the past, students gain a greater appreciation of the current media landscape and, perhaps, the ability to adapt quickly to the future.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
