           <li class="courseListItem" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0 0 10px;list-style-image:none;list-style-type:none;">
           









  
    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/221.html" title="RTA 221 - Experiential Media/Interdisciplinary Practice" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 221</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Experiential Media/Interdisciplinary Practice</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces students to fundamental theories from a range of disciplines that illuminate how the senses, identity, social context, and physical environment shape our experience of art, design, and popular culture. Students learn how to use theories to examine contemporary art and reflect on relevant issues such as how new media's computational and networked technologies inform and transform our experience of cultural content.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
