    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/310.html" title="RTA 310 - Media Aesthetics and Culture" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 310</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Media Aesthetics and Culture</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course is designed to broaden understanding of the relationship between culture and media. Students tackle theories and ideas of visual studies, gender, fandom, transmedia, heroism and representation in all different media from TV to webisodes to gaming to comics and music. Students will learn about historical and current examples of boundary-breaking storytelling, and analyze and critique the work of storytellers from the past and present.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
