    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/321.html" title="RTA 321 - Intro to Tangible Media" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 321</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Intro to Tangible Media</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Using the human body and its senses (vision, acoustic, touch, taste, smell, proprioception - physical sense of self movement) as an organizing model, this course introduces students to Physical Computing practices. Students will learn about digital and analog sensor systems, be introduced to micro-controllers, computer sensor systems and ubiquitous computing. Basic programming skills are an important part of this course.</div>
	
	
