		<div class="courseListDescription">This course examines how media technologies relate to racialized, gendered and sexualized bodies.  Students consider scholarly and popular works ranging from the cinematic representation of Frankenstein to current studies of cyborgian bodies in order to produce creative work that responds to modern and postmodern ideas about the body.</div>
	
	
