		<div class="courseListDescription">Most of us are online most of the time. How do marginalized communities fare in this virtual space?  This course will present an exciting roster of media artists/theorists from Aboriginal, LGBT, feminist and racialized communities, who use research and creation to forge alternate discourses and visual/virtual worlds. We will also engage with art and theory on social justice media and activism.</div>
	
	
