    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/903.html" title="RTA 903 - News and Current Affairs Theory" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 903</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">News and Current Affairs Theory</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">News as entertainment information, satire, social instructor: audiences interact with the news in many ways. We look critically at ideas like discourse, news value and news filters, and then learn scholarly tools for analyzing news and its audiences. From radio to tabloid journals to E-zines to Twitter, we open up the idea of news in the 21st century, and think about its history, meanings, and future. War news and digital media are a particular focus.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListUnits"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Billing Units: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1</span></div>
	
    
        <div class="courseListCount" ><span class="courseInfoLabels">Count: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
    
    
	
	
	
	
	


