		<div class="courseListDescription"><p>This course focuses on the role of the production manager in film and&nbsp;television. Students will become acquainted with all aspects of a&nbsp;production: development; pre-production; production; post-production.&nbsp;Topics will include legal aspects, financing, insurance, script breakdown&nbsp;and scheduling, budgeting, accounting and cost reports, location&nbsp;management, talent and crew unions, contracts, reporting mechanisms and relevant forms and paperwork as well as a review of key production personnel job descriptions and tips on getting hired.&nbsp;</p>
