    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/929.html" title="RTA 929 - Multi-platform Narrative" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 929</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Multi-platform Narrative</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">In this studio course, as students develop interactive, nonlinear and transmedia narratives, they are tasked with finding the best platform(s) for each story, as they explore the interplay of medium and narrative. Students will be given a series of projects and narrative design challenges, wherein they must choose the media with which to best convey the narrative goals. Topics explored include the narrative impact of private versus public content, scale and screens, and the use of social networks, ubiquitous media, and "real" space to tell compelling stories.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lab: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
