    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/955.html" title="RTA 955 - Sports Broadcasting" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 955</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Sports Broadcasting</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course examines the programming philosophy and production of sports programs. The course explores different types of programming including feature production, sports journalism, live-event coverage and interactive Web-based production. It will discuss the behind the scenes responsibilities of executives, editorial staff and technical crews, as well as on air-performance and visual presentation in both traditional and interactive environments. Using this knowledge, students will produce a sports feature and a live production. (Formerly BDC 955).</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
