    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/media/RTA/972.html" title="RTA 972 - Sound Synthesis" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RTA 972</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Sound Synthesis</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course will cover practices and principles of analog and digital sound synthesis and their historic origins; related audio equipment and applications; theories of sound samplers; algorithmic composition; synthesizers and sequencers; computer music; digital signal processing; computer synchronization; and MIDI applications in sound synthesis and recording production. Advanced sound synthesis techniques are studied and supplemented with sound synthesis studio laboratory work.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lab: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
